md3.md3model
Class AnimationType

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--md3.md3model.AnimationType
public class AnimationType
extends java.lang.Object

This class defines the different animation types that can be applied to a MD3 model. The class uses the typesafe enum pattern.

Author:
Erwin Vervaet (klr8@fragland.net)

Field Detail

LEGS

public static final AnimationType LEGS

The animation is only applicable to the LEGS submodel of a composed model. This submodel is normally the top level model, loaded from a file lower.md3.

TORSO

public static final AnimationType TORSO

The animation is only applicable to the TORSO submodel of a composed model. The TORSO submodel is normally loaded from a file upper.md3.

BOTH

public static final AnimationType BOTH

The animation is applicable to BOTH the LEGS and TORSO submodels of a composed model.

ALL

public static final AnimationType ALL

The animation is applicable to all submodels.
